\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Who might you be and how did you find me?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>My name is Manu, and I came searching for you Mr. Esbeche.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Stop with the mister and call me Esbeche. I am not that too old to be called mister, but not too young to be junior.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>So why did you come here to find me lad? Is my restaurant dirty? THAT TOMAS I TOLD HIM TO-
\n<Manu><WordWrap>I came looking for you because of the contest.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>But after everything I went through to find you, why is your asnwer still no? And why did you abandoned everything?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Your restaurant, the people of this island, the contest and even Tomas. Why did you do it and why now out of all days?
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>You are persistent and quite a difficult person to handle.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Fine I'll tell you but don't come crying after.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>The answer is simple Manu...Everything is now meaningless.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>What's the point of being a so called "Chef" if your just after the fame and glory. Not only that but cooking itself has lost its meaning and purpose.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>People come to Gastropolis to "compete" but are just after the fame and glory.

\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>If people were so passionate about cooking rather than building a franchise till the bitter end, then tell me. Name a person who won from the Gastropolis contest and decided not to make a franchise out of their name and reputation.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Even you yourself is speachless to what I had said.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Cooking has lost its virtue of being a people's culture and identity. Now its just mimicry and souless journey of food that doesn't bring the name of our heritage.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>If your planning on bringing me back, you best have a good reason as to why.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>So what will it be then kid?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Please comeback to the restaruant and continue the contest.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>People have risked their live's to find you and got trapped in caves.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Please Esbeche, come back this one time. I need to continue my culinary journey.

\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>If I were to comeback and just let you move on to the next area. Wouldn't it be unfair and cheating since I'm allowing you only to proceed? Forget about it. I am not leaving for one second.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>You better have a better reason to get me back to the contest.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>If I can bring your favorite dish here, right in front of your face, will you come back?
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>My favorite dish eh? Hmmm...I have two favorite dishes I want you to make.

\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>First is Kinilaw, a raw tuna dish that is cooked using the acidity of calamansi and vinegar that makes the dish have a profound sour taste to it and the tuna having a soft yet firm texture.

\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Second is Grilled Bangus, a trademark fish of the Philippines that is profound with it's flavorful belly. Grilling brings out the charness of the fish and the unique flavor of the bangus comes out.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>If you can bring me my favorite dish, maybe I'll reconsider comming back to the restaurant. But prove it to me.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Find Tomas and he'll help you with making the dish.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>There's a cave below this place, it's a shortcut. Head right there and you'll be able to reach the other side of the ave safely.
Head back to Esbeche's restaurant and talk to Tomas.

\n<Manu><WordWrap>Then I challenge you to a cooking contest!
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Interesting proposition Manu. What are the terms and condition of this challenge?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>We cook what available food you have in your restaurant and you choose what food we will cook.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>The dish I choose is Sinigang. But I'll make it challenging for us both.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>We will only have 3 minutes to complete making the Sinigang.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Scared and worried Manu? You can still step away from this. This is your last chance.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Fine its a deal! I'll win this challenge.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Head back to the restaurant so we can start the challenge.

\n<Manu><WordWrap>Yes Esbeche, I have made the dishes for you.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Good now present me the Kinilaw Manu.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Here it is Esbeche, the Kinilaw you have requested to make.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>The Tuna taste freshly caught and the flavors are blending well...
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Spicy and sour at the same time, I like that. It brings out the flavor of the dish, though many hate it for its very sour flavor, but personally I like it too nmuch.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>As requested, here is the Grilled Bangus.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>The taste of this Grilled Bangus is delightful. Fresh and the smokey flavor of the charred from the grill brgins out the sweetness of the fish.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>I am a bit impressed that you were able to execute this dish. But that still leaves me with an indecisive answer for you.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>I know You want to be a great chef Manu, I truly believe that.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>You still have a lot to prove, but you are persistant in your dreams.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>You may not be the most talented nor the skilled, but you do have a dream and a clear focus on what you want.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>Then it is decided. I'll allow you to proceed to the next area of the contest.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>You have proven to me the lenghts of a person will do in order to achieve their dreams.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>And you have proven me that. So, congratulations Manu you can now continue your journey to becomming a chef.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>I don't really know what to say Esbeche...
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>No need to think, just hurry along and reach the next area of the contest.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Before that, how would I tell the people that I am allowed to proceed to the next area of the contest? And what about you Esbeche? aren't you going to return to your restaurant?
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>The restaurant can wait for a while...I am in no rush.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>And for the approval of your "legitimate" access to the next area, just tell them that I said so.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>People take my words seriously, so I doubt that they would second guess what I said.
\n<Esbeche><WordWrap>So head on out to the next area of the contest Manu. May your dreams come true.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>I am greatful Esbeche and I won't fail you.
You can now roam the island as you please
